1. Copy config/database.default.yml to config/database.yml and edit accordingly
2. rake db:migrate (preceded by rake db:create if the database doesn't already exist)
3. rake seek:repop_cv - this prepopultes the database with a dummy user and a predefined list of tags assigned to them

if using search

4. make a config/environment_local.rb file, and add to it "SOLR_ENABLED=true"
5. make sure the directories "vendor/plugins/acts_as_solr/solr/log" and "vendor/plugins/acts_as_solr/solr/tmp" exist
6. rake solr:resolr
7. rake solr:start to start database server